onArray (wrapping the ndarray for pandas integration) → scipy.stats.pearsonr (accepting the array for statistical analysis and generating correlation metrics).\n\nThis architecture enables seamless composition: users can aggregate raw data using NumPy's core functions, wrap the results in pandas extension arrays for tabular data manipulation, and then apply sophisticated statistical analysis through SciPy's functions on the same underlying data structures."
